Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer
exclusive Copyright and Related Rights upon the creator and subsequent
owner(s) of an original work of authorship and/or a database. Certain
owners wish to permanently relinquish those rights to a Work for the
purpose of contributing to a commons of creative, cultural and scientific
works that the public can reliably and freely build upon.

1. Waiver. To the greatest extent permitted by applicable law, Affirmer
hereby waives all Copyright and Related Rights in the Work.

2. Public License Fallback. Should any part of the Waiver be judged
legally invalid, Affirmer grants a royalty-free, non-transferable,
non-sublicensable, non-exclusive, irrevocable and unconditional license
to exercise Copyright and Related Rights in the Work for any purpose.

3. No trademark or patent rights held by Affirmer are waived.
Affirmer offers the Work as-is with no warranties of any kind.
